This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel neural network architecture that improves the robustness of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks. The paper also discusses the theoretical foundation of the proposed method, which is related to linear discriminant analysis (LDA), a well-known technique in machine learning. Additionally, the paper uses datasets from computer vision (MNIST, CIFAR-10) and natural language processing (IMDB) domains, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of adversarial attacks, which may also make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
